ResourceHeader.Description: 1: The Interstellar Boundary Explorer (IBEX) has operated in space since 2008 updating our knowledge of the outer heliosphere and its interaction with the local interstellar medium. Start-time: 2008-12-25. There are currently 16 releases of IBEX-HI and/or IBEX-LO data covering 2009-2019. 2: This data set is from the Release 7 (1 year-cadence) IBEX-Hi map data for the years 2009-2013 in the form of ram-directionl ENA (hydrogen) fluxes with Compton-Getting correction (cg) of flux spectra for spacecraft motion and no correction for ENA survival probability (nosp) between 1 and 100 AU. 3. The data consist of all-sky maps in Solar Ecliptic Longitude (east and west) and Latitude angles for ENA (hydrogen) fluxes from IBEX-Hi energy bands 2-6 in numerical data form. Energy channels 2-6 have FWHM ranges of 0.52-0.95, 0.84-1.55, 1.36-2.50, 1.99-3.75, 3.13-6.00 keV, respectively. The corresponding center-point energies are 0.71, 1.11, 1.74, 2.73, and 4.29 keV. Details of the data and enabled science from Release 10 are given in the following journal publication: 4: McComas, D. J., et al. (2017), Seven Years of Imaging the Global Heliosphere with IBEX, Astrophys. J. Supp. Ser., 229(2), 41 (32 pp.), 5: http://doi.org/10.3847/1538-4365/aa66d8 6. The following codes are used to define dataset types: cg = Compton-Getting corrections have been applied to the data to account for the speed of the spacecraft relative to the direction of arrival of the ENAs. nocg = no Compton-Getting corrections sp = survival probability corrections have been applied to the data to account for the loss of ENAs due to radiation pressure, photoionization and ionization via charge exchange with solar wind protons as they stream through the heliosphere. This correction scales the data out from IBEX at 1 AU to ~100 AU. In the original data this mode is denoted as Tabular. noSP - no survival probability corrections have been applied to the data. omni = data from all directions. ram = data was collected when the spacecraft was ramming into the incoming ENAs. antiram = data was collected when the spacecraft was moving away from the incoming ENAs. 7. The following list associates Release 16 map numbers (1-22) with mission year (1-9), orbits (11-471b), and dates (12/25/2008-12/26/2019): Map 1: Map2009A, year 1, orbits 11-34, dates 12/25/2008-06/25/2009 Map 2: Map2009B, year 1, orbits 35-58, dates 06/25/2009-12/25/2009 Map 3: Map2010A, year 2, orbits 59-82, dates 12/25/2009-06/26/2010 Map 4: Map2010B, year 2, orbits 83-106, dates 06/26/2010-12/26/2010 Map 5: Map2011A, year 3, orbits 107-130a, dates 12/26/2010-06/25/2011 Map 6: Map2011B, year 3, orbits 130b-150a, dates 06/25/2011-12/24/2011 Map 7: Map2012A, year 4, orbits 150b-170a, dates 12/24/2011-06/22/2012 Map 8: Map2012B, year 4, orbits 170b-190b, dates 06/22/2012-12/26/2012 Map 9: Map2013A, year 5, orbits 191a-210b, dates 12/26/2012-06/26/2013 Map 10: Map2013B, year 5, orbits 211a-230b, dates 06/26/2013-12/26/2013 Map 11: Map2014A, year 6, orbits 231a-250b, dates 12/26/2013-06/26/2014 Map 12: Map2014B, year 6, orbits 251a-270b, dates 06/26/2014-12/24/2014 Map 13: Map2015A, year 7, orbits 271a-290b, dates 12/24/2014-06/24/2015 Map 14: Map2015B, year 7, orbits 291a-310b, dates 06/24/2015-12/23/2015 Map 15: Map2016A, year 8, orbits 311a-330b, dates 12/24/2015 . 06/23/2016 Map 16: Map2016B, year 8, orbits 331a-351a, dates 06/24/2016 . 12/26/2016 Map 17: Map2017A, year 9, orbits 351b-371a, dates 12/26/2016 . 06/24/2017 Map 18: Map2017B, year 9, orbits 371b-391a, dates 06/25/2017 . 12/25/2017 Map 19: Map2018A, year 10, orbits 391b-411b, dates 12/25/2017 . 06/28/2018 Map 20: Map2018B, year 10, orbits 412a-431b, dates 06/29/2018 . 12/26/2018 Map 21: Map2019A, year 11, orbits 432a-451b, dates 12/27/2018 . 06/27/2019 Map 22: Map2019B, year 11, orbits 452a-471b, dates 06/28/2019 . 12/26/2019 8: This particular data set, denoted in the original ascii files as hvset_noSP_ram_cg_yearN for N=1,5, includes pixel map data from ram direction (ram-directional), CG, no SP, 1 year cadence.

Parameter.Name: Epoch
Parameter.Description: CDF epoch time for the start of the one-year measurement period
Parameter.Caveats: This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: Epoch2
Parameter.Description: CDF epoch time for end of the measurement period in a one-year map
Parameter.Caveats: This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: Starting Map Number
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Sequential starting number 1 - 22 for six-month map from IBEX Data Release 16
Parameter.Caveats: 6-month maps 1 - 22 cover the years of data 2009-2019. The yearly data takes average of two consecutive maps.

Parameter.Name: Solar Ecliptic Latitude Bin Number
Parameter.Description: Solar Ecliptic Latitude Bin Number corresponding to six-degree latitudinal increments of the current IBEX-HI viewing sector
Parameter.Caveats: There are 30 angular bins in Solar Ecliptic Latitude ( -90 to +90 degrees). The center-point degree value for Bin 1 is -87 degrees and for Bin 30 is +87 degrees.

Parameter.Name: Solar West Ecliptic Longitude Bin Number
Parameter.Description: Solar West Ecliptic Longitude Bin Number corresponding to six-degree longitudinal increments of the current IBEX-HI viewing sector
Parameter.Caveats: There are 60 angular sectors in Solar West Ecliptic Longitude from 0 to 360 degrees. The first Number Bin = 1 corresponds to a mid-point longitude angle of 3 degrees, the last = 30 to 357 degrees.

Parameter.Name: Solar Ecliptic Latitude
Parameter.Caveats: Latitude value corresponds to the mid-point of six-degree latitudinal IBEX-HI viewing sector

Parameter.Name: Solar West Ecliptic Longitude
Parameter.Caveats: Longitude value corresponds to the mid-point of six-degree longitudinal IBEX-HI viewing sector.

Parameter.Name: Solar East Ecliptic Longitude
Parameter.Caveats: Longitude value corresponds to the mid-point of six-degree longitudinal IBEX-HI viewing sector.

Parameter.Name: Starting Orbit Number
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Starting Orbit Number of the measurement period
Parameter.Caveats: IBEX orbital period around Earth is 7.5 days.

Parameter.Name: Ending Orbit Number
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: Ending Orbit Number of the measurement period
Parameter.Caveats: IBEX orbital period around Earth is 7.5 days
